{
  "text": "Xyridaceae usually emerges as a sister group of Eriocaulaceae, and also related to Mayacaceae in the xyrid clade (Givinish et al. 2010) . However, its phylogenetic affinities have not been fully established and its monophyly has already been questioned [CITATION_1] . The most recent phylogenies support the family as a sister group of Eriocaulaceae [CITATION_2] or as sister of the clade formed by the restiids and graminids [CITATION_3] . The lack of detailed phylogenies focusing on the Neotropical species will be addressed soon with ongoing researche (Motta 2014).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "7896271",
